title: F1 Enterable — player can enter an enterable thing
story: chord-f1-enterable
description: ADR-218 §1a (ratchet F1) — the `enterable` trait adjective composes
  EnterableTrait, closing the `entering` action gap. The cage carries only the
  `enterable` adjective (no container), so a successful `enter` proves the
  adjective alone made the thing enterable.
---

# The enterable cage is present and describable.
> examine cage
[OK: contains "iron cage"]

# `enter` succeeds because `enterable` composed EnterableTrait (preposition `in`).
> enter cage
[OK: contains "into the cage"]
